42.a4 that would create several irrational moves for the
remainder of the game. The Russian tournament book by
N.I. Grekov confirms that 42.a3 was in fact the move played. } 42... Rh7 43. Ba5 Rh8 44. Bb4 Rc8 45. Ba5 Ng5 46. Bd2 Ne4 47. Ba5 Kg6 48. Bb4 f5 49. Ba5 Rh8 50. Ke3 Re8 51. Kd3 Rc8 52. Bb4 Rc7 53. Ba5 Rh7 54. Ke3 Re7 55. Kd3 f4 56. gxf4 Rh7 57. Bd2 Nxd2 58. Kxd2 Rh3 59. f3 gxf3 60. Rf2 Kf5 61. Ke3 Kg4 62. b4 Rh1 63. f5 Re1+ 64. Kd3 Re4 { 0-1 Black wins. } 0-1


